cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on learning dexterous robotic policies and transferring them to new robots with different hardware properties. 
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is also likely as the paper proposes a novel approach using deep reinforcement learning to train a universal policy conditioned on a vector representation of robot hardware. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is another possible category as the paper deals with learning and transferring policies for robots in simulation. 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) could be a relevant category as the paper mentions using visual input for some of the tasks. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also a possible category as the paper deals with controlling robots with different dynamics and kinematic structures.
